  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Welcome to Aximar!\n\nPress **Shift+Enter** to run each code cell.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "2 + 3 * 5",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Variables and assignment\n\nUse `:` to assign values to variables.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "n: 42;\nn^2 + n + 1",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Clear a variable with `kill()` when you're done with it. It becomes symbolic again.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "kill(n)$\nn + 1",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Symbolic algebra",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "expand((x + y)^3)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Calculus\n\nDifferentiation and integration:",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "diff(sin(x) * exp(x), x)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "integrate(x^2 * exp(-x), x)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Solving equations",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "solve(x^2 - 5*x + 6 = 0, x)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Matrices",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "A: matrix([1, 2], [3, 4]);\ndeterminant(A)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Simplification",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "trigsimp(sin(x)^2 + cos(x)^2)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Math symbols\n\nType `\\` followed by a name (e.g. `\\alpha`, `\\theta`) to insert Unicode symbols.\nThey are automatically translated to Maxima when you evaluate.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "θ: %pi/4;\nsin(θ)^2 + cos(θ)^2",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "f: α*x^2 + β*x + γ;\nsolve(f = 0, x)",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Tips\n\n- Press **Cmd+K** (or **Ctrl+K**) to open the function browser\n- Click **suggestion chips** below outputs for next steps\n- Use `$x^2$` in markdown cells for inline math: $x^2 + y^2 = r^2$",
      "metadata": {}
    }
  ]
